    <title type="html"><![CDATA[Strategy Pattern with Dependency Injection]]></title>
    <link href="http://uhaciogullari.github.io/blog/2014/01/05/strategy-pattern-with-dependency-injection/"/>
    <updated>2014-01-05T13:08:22-08:00</updated>
    <id>http://uhaciogullari.github.io/blog/2014/01/05/strategy-pattern-with-dependency-injection</id>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p><a href="http://sourcemaking.com/design_patterns/strategy">Strategy pattern</a> is one of the most useful design patterns in OOP. It lets you select an algoritm&rsquo;s implementation at runtime. However most of the examples you will find online won&rsquo;t make sense if you are using dependency injection. Here&rsquo;s one of them:</p>

<figure class='code'><figcaption><span></span></figcaption><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
